(1, 12, 'you can hug a woman', 5),
(1, 24, 'I would write a more indepth review, but im too busy playing Elden Ring.', 5),
(1, 36, 'Bring bloodborne to PC', 5),
(1, 41, 'I started the journey as a lowly tarnished, with only the guidance of grace to guide me on a perilous path of struggle, hardship and suffering. I stumbled, I failed and I died. I came back up again, learning from my mistakes.\r\nIn the journey, I faced many great enemies. Some I admired and respected while some I loathed and hated, yet thankful for them all.\r\nI made friends, learned from teachers, faced-off adversaries, fell in love, cried in loss, and shared on the happiness of each and every characters of the game. For those who may call me their consort, their lambkin, their tarnished, or even their lord; i express my thanks.\r\n\r\nThis game was my second entry to fromsoftwares, ( the first being sekiro), and I am at a loss of words to express the emotional rollercoaster I went through during my playthroughs. I now understand why their games are so well-celebrated and has such a vast community.\r\n\r\nIt doesn\'t matter if I am a lowly tanished, I shall never put my foolish ambitions to rest.', 5),
(2, 3, 'i was looking for something new to play and saw this game suggested but for $20 i wasn\'t really sure. i found it for $10 and figured screw it, the description on the store page seems interesting enough.\r\n\r\ni\'ve never immediately loved a game as much as i did this when i first opened it and got blasted by that harmonica\r\n\r\nwent from only vaguely knowing persona through smash bros to now having played 3fes,4g,5, and 4AU, read the manga of the first game, gonna start the second games soon, and seen all the animes (seen the 4 and 4g animes 3 times)\r\n\r\n+best characters in any game ever (idk what real life social interaction looks like)\r\n+chad life sim (i have no life)\r\n+great themes (dad left me)\r\n+pretty good story (never interacted with woman)\r\n+cringe <3 (this is a cry for help)\r\n\r\nwatch the animes too when you\'re done', 5),
(2, 20, 'My wife left me.', 5),
(2, 23, 'Persona 4 is so good i wish social interaction was real', 4),
(2, 26, 'the real persona 4 golden was the friends we made along the way', 5),
(2, 30, 'Blown away by how good this game has been so far. I\'ve never been one to get into JRPG type games but this is potentially turning me around if others meet this quality.', 5),
(2, 32, 'This game made me get a degree in Psychology (I wish I was joking).', 5),
(3, 3, 'After all these years I\'m still enjoying the 1000000000p* graphics with the high-resolution super texture technology that the modern human eyeballs can\'t even comprehend and see with frame rates up to 21000 per milliseconds, and the state of the art ragdoll physics and particle explosion future systems put in place.\r\n\r\nThere is all so workshop to make and build your own levels while using their advanced manipulation engine to control what you see on screen and there\'s stuff to collect and brag about when you see the mindblowing realistic hair simulation.\r\n\r\nI\'m still waiting for the oculus rift support with up to x5 simultaneous oculuses with video card mega graphic throttling with ram, processors, sound effects when your characters do stuff.\r\n\r\nBut seriously I wish I had the bestest of best friends like Hatty Hattington to go on many adventures with or just to play games with, time to play some more after I buckle my pants.', 5),
(3, 19, 'The only time I\'ve ever really tried to get an A+...sad really.', 5),
(3, 24, 'I absolutely love this game. I used to play it when I was little, so it really feels nostalgic, and brings back the good times.', 5),
(3, 34, NULL, NULL),
(3, 41, '---{ Graphics }---\n☐ You forget what reality is\n☐ Beautiful\n☑ Good\n☐ Decent\n☐ Bad\n☐ Don‘t look too long at it\n☐ MS-DOS\n\n---{ Gameplay }---\n☑ Very good\n☐ Good\n☐ It\'s just gameplay\n☐ Mehh\n☐ Watch paint dry instead\n☐ Just don\'t\n\n---{ Audio }---\n☐ Eargasm\n☑ Very good\n☐ Good\n☐ Not too bad\n☐ Bad\n☐ I\'m now deaf', 4),
(3, 42, NULL, NULL),
(4, 1, 'Loving the game so far. It\'s my first Forza game ever so I have no other ones to compare it to. Played good with keyboard, plays better with a racing sim setup. Top notch lighting / graphics. Map is pretty cool, would have preferred a more urban setting. Tons of cars to acquire & customize. There\'s more performance upgrades than visual. User interface is pretty bad. Game is very vibrant and colorful down to the menus. While being arcade-y, it\'s a solid driving game.. Just ignore the npc\'s and dialogue.', 4),
(4, 3, 'Edited after playing the game further.\r\n---{ Graphics }---\r\n☑ You forget what reality is (It is fantastic, no other racing games till date has this gorgeous and detailed graphics)\r\n☐ Beautiful\r\n☐ Good\r\n☐ Decent\r\n☐ Bad\r\n☐ Don‘t look too long at it\r\n☐ MS-DOS\r\n\r\n---{ Gameplay }---\r\n☑ Very good (Huge list of cars having very detailed tuning, variety of races and tons of exploration. You won\'t get bored so soon.)\r\n☐ Good\r\n☐ It\'s just gameplay\r\n☐ Mehh\r\n☐ Watch paint dry instead\r\n☐ Just don\'t\r\n\r\n---{ Audio }---\r\n☐ Eargasm\r\n☑ Very good (I can say it is good, the song selection playlist does go well with fast pace racing or while cruising around Mexico)\r\n☐ Good\r\n☐ Not too bad\r\n☐ Bad\r\n☐ I\'m now deaf\r\n\r\n---{ Audience }---\r\n☑ Everyone (Regardless of age I think everyone can enjoy this game)\r\n☐ Teens\r\n☐ Adults\r\n☐ Grandma', 4),
(4, 4, 'It\'s basically Forza Horizon 4.5.\r\n\r\nThe map is new, the graphics are slightly better, most cars are carried over from previous games in the series, and gameplay modes are almost exactly the same as in Horizon 4. There are some quality of life improvements in the UI, some new multiplayer-centric activities, but overall it plays the same as the previous game. That itself is not a bad thing, as obviously the devs stick to the tried-and-tested formula that works. But this time it feels like they played it too safe. Who knows, maybe the DLC will introduce more new content and changes, while the devs focus until now was to get the base game done ready for the November release slot.\r\n\r\nTo sum up:\r\n- If you haven\'t played Horizon 4, buy that one on sale instead of 5. It looks almost as good, it\'s sold at a good discount, it has more content and less bugs, and the online community is still active.\r\n- if you liked Horizon 4 or you want to run with the cool kids and play the newest game, then I can recommend Horizon 5.\r\n- if you didn\'t like previous Horizon games, there\'s nothing new here that will change your mind.', 4),
