(14, 5, 'Fallout 3 was a huge advancement in the Fallout franchise as it switched from a 2D Turn-based RPG to a 3D FPS game. Some prefer the older games and that’s understandable but I have enjoyed these 3D Fallout games. I still plan on playing the original Fallout games but that’s beside the point. Getting back to the topic of Fallout 3, this game is good. Is it Fallout: New Vegas levels of good? No. It’s still good nonetheless. The story was very okay. It was interesting enough but I didn’t think was written too well and it doesn’t compare to New Vegas. The game doesn’t shine in its main questline but where it does shine is in some of its side quests and the atmosphere/exploring.\r\n\r\nI’ve already spoken of the main questline but it follows you, a former vault resident, who escapes in search of his father. The intro mission itself was great. It set up relationships and it showed part of living in a vault. After this, the main quest kind of goes downhill. It doesn’t end up horrible but it gives no reason to care for the characters and the only motivation for me was to see it through as the plot was interesting enough. The story isn’t as open as NV in choice and it doesn’t have factions or anything like that. It pretty much forces you to see one faction as all good and another as all bad but even then, it doesn’t let you join the evil faction. Without getting into details, my favourite mainline quest has to be Tranquility Lane.', 3),
(14, 7, 'First off let me state that this game WILL NOT WORK unless you go into the game files and make some modifications. The fact that this game is unplayable from the box is unacceptable. BUT, if you do get the game working you will have a fun time. Although Fallout 3 is not as in depth with its RPG mechanics as New Vegas it is still worth a play. If your coming to this game for a great story your not gonna find it. Instead you should expect an extremely atmospheric dungeon crawler with decent RPG elements. This game has PLENTY of content for you to enjoy if your willing to explore and find it. Many people tend to write off Fallout 3 for it\'s faults, but personally I am thankful for it\'s existence and for the other games it has spawned as a direct result. Fallout 3 is not perfect, but it is still a really good time.\r\n\r\nHere is a video that might help you if your having trouble getting the game to run:\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RDTViZGRhJo&list=PLXJDzamV-4AO7EsKUI4ZyIy7gXAGdVzXz&index=20', 4),
