(15, 2, 'I really think this is one of my favorite game of this style I\'ve ever played.\r\nIt feels different than DOOM Eternal, and I honestly prefer this game, you have less mobility but you feel stronger, it\'s a weird feeling to explain. The graphics are BEAUTIFUL as always, and the gameplay is just too satisfying.\r\nI\'d definitely recommend you playing this game, you won\'t regret it.', 5),
(15, 4, 'I always avoid reviewing this game because I thought I would do it injustice. This game by all means, is THE GREATEST OF ALL TIMES. People love Doom Eternal, me too. But DOOM has an atmosphere that will make you feel like you are ripping & tearing. Doom Eternal is all about Gameplay, this game is about Atmosphere. From the get-go you\'ll realized you are not going to screw around. You realized you are gonna make demons pay, and you don\'t care for what.\r\nThe graphics are amazing, the atmosphere, the feeling of horror and danger is amazing, but the thing is, the horror of Doom isn\'t there to scare you, it\'s there to motivate you. To motivate you to clean this mess. Rarely ever do you get a jumpscare, hell, you even jumpscare demons yourself. The graphics are carefully done to make sure you feel on the edge, even if you really aren\'t.\r\nI have nothing to say about Snapmap or Multiplayer because I have tried none. But from what I heard Snapmap was full of potential and just not discovered properly, and the MP follows the classic Doom MP trope which is exciting and oldschool.\r\nThe Arcade mode is one of my favorites though. You pass the levels you previously did on the Story Mode, only to be rewarded by the percentage of you kill. It\'s neat, worthwhile and exceptionally fun.\r\nNOW THE GAMEPLAY, OH BOY THE GAMEPLAY. You feel like an absolute TITAN. Demons are trapped in arenas with you, expecting their epic failures.', 5),
(15, 7, '♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ this game is just pure, exciting action. The music, the arena-like level design, the weapon switching, the impact of said weapons, the never-ending movement requirement, its all just there to make the demon killing experience ♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥♥ blissful.\r\n\r\nIf I had to force myself to think about something bad... well, I didn\'t care for the secrets scattered about the levels towards the end, though the early ones were pretty interesting. The ones at the start especially might require you to look around a bit, reason about the layout of the level, etc, whereas towards the end they are either very hard to find or, most of the time, literally just in front of you as you make it through the level.\r\n\r\nWhat else... idk, its just demon killing action, and its lovely.\r\n\r\nOh, the voice talking about the past of the hell guy demon dude thingamajig just puts a smile on my face. It meshes so well with the action of the game: over the top, cool, heroic, and just fun.', 4),
