(15, 40, 'DOOM is a masterpiece. Very little can be faulted; it perfectly understood what it wanted to be. Just enough story to feel like your actions mattered, a very self-aware sense of humour, rewarding secrets/upgrades, great special effects, fun and varied level/arena design, amazing music, great level of difficulty, and stacks of great looking monsters.\r\n\r\nIt shines all the more when replaying after its sequel, Eternal, which is a mixed bag. This game is minimalist in comparison, and a more cohesive experience for it.\r\n\r\nI think DOOM 2016 is one of the few games I\'ve ever played that I would give a 10/10. It does what it sets out to do, and it\'s amazing fun.', 5),
