(27, 39, 'atmosphere is dark and oppressive, story is great, gameplay is fantastic', 5),
(27, 42, NULL, NULL),
(28, 7, 'Before continuing further, this review is ONLY based off what I experienced in the co-op portion of the game. Based off of what I experienced I do not recommend this game to anyone looking for a singleplayer experience.\r\n\r\nDead Space as a franchise has never really stood out to me as something I\'d enjoy, as I don\'t get much from horror games, so perhaps it\'s due to a lack of context that I find this game to actually be quite good. Throughout my entire playthrough of Dead Space 3 I felt that the game was a long-lost brother or sequel of the Lost Planet series, actually making intuitive usage of the co-op features implemented into the game. I wholeheartedly feel that if this game had been released as its own series rather than carrying the Dead Space franchise\' name, it would\'ve been much more successful.\r\n\r\nTruthfully I don\'t have a whole lot bad to say about my experience with this game, as it felt like a non-stop riot throughout the entire experience, with my friend and I having a blast the entire time.\r\n', 3),
(28, 9, 'Did it kill the franchise?... Yes\r\nIs it a good game?...Yes', 4),
(28, 19, 'I don\'t get why this gets the hate it does. It was a really fun coop game. I wish they\'d continue the series and keep the two player campaign.', 5),
(28, 20, 'I haven\'t played the previous games, so the details of the story is a bit lost on me. That said... For as violent as this game is, it\'s pretty Saturday Morning Cartoon-levels of simple. It\'s not scary, just grotesque. it\'s a very mindless shooter, but it works well and feels satisfying enough. I hesitate to recommend it, but if you just want to walk around an alien planet and shoot aliens this won\'t disappoint you...', 4),
(28, 41, NULL, NULL),
(29, 7, 'Darkest chapter? more like THAT WAS IT? chapter\r\n\r\nThe addon is fun, and the environment looks orgasmic, but the ending\r\n\r\nThe ENDING\r\n\r\nIT SUCKS HARD\r\n\r\nIt\'s either all a hallucination or everything was for nothing. I legit headcannoned this addon out of my desired canon. Having Carver and Isaac fight on the planet till they drop doom style is probably better than this ending. It\'s a total downer, but at least I got some free MK-lls with it.\r\n\r\nEven if it makes sense that it may be impossible to stop the moons, I just don\'t like it. Get this for the achievements and never play it again. The concepts in the addon were kinda cool though, not gonna lie and at least carver gets some more lines to say like the amazing man that he is.', 3),
(29, 9, 'This DLC is totally unnecessary and should\'ve been in the main game or at least as a free dlc, It is extremely short. if you still want to know what happens after the main ending just go and watch on youtube. its another clifhanger anyways.', 1),
(29, 19, 'It\'s good, not 10 bucks good, but good.', 3),
(29, 20, 'Hard coop campaign was a great experience for me, One of my best ever. Even after previous solo play through.', 4);
