(33, 3, '>Worked on gathering resources for 20+ hours\r\n>Made a base\r\n>Saw no one used landmines\r\n>Went a little overboard, crafted a hundred+ landmines\r\n>Surrounded my base with said landmines (outside was all tall grass in the middle of a forest) and armored every single wall and floor, adding traps to every nook and cranny of it\r\n>Attracted the attention of a large clan\r\n>They started trying to raid me, only to be met with the hundred landmines around the place, making them constantly die to them\r\n>The explosions attract more players, which proceed to counter said clan and then get killed themselves by landmines\r\n(Fun fact landmines destroy items in your inventory)\r\n>I stand and watch as they use dozens and dozens of rockets and explosive ammo to get in the bunker, seemingly using all that they have, hoping to get in and find good loot to compensate for what they\'ve spent\r\n>They finally break the last set of honeycombed, armored walls and find the TC\r\n>The TC has nothing but a thousand metal scrap and some high quality metal\r\n>I had used every single resource I had to make a group of people lose hundreds of hours of their work and get less than nothing in return\r\n\r\n11/10 would do a little trolling again.', 4),
(33, 8, 'Very intense and action packed, MUST have a high mental capacity, your sanity is constantly being\r\ntested. Its a good game once you get the hang of things, though the whole process can be very time consuming.\r\nI would rate the in game community a 6.5 out of 10, it is possible to find a a non toxic person but the ratio of\r\nthat and encountering a toxic one heavily favors the toxic side. Game is a 8.3 out of 10 overall.', 4),
