(34, 8, 'I hooked up the USB/MIDI adapter between my Yamaha Clavinova Digital Piano and my PC, then logged into rust and enabled the Midi function under settings > experimental. Then I ran straight to outpost and hopped on the Wheelbarrow Piano...and voila! It worked perfectly (with the exception of damper pedal). Thanks FP, this is the best thing since sliced cheese!', 5),
(35, 2, 'PREFACE:\r\n\r\nI will start this by saying that you might find yourself looking at my \"hours played\" tag and either groan or stare confused. Yes, undoubtedly I play D2 quite a lot. I was going for an inside joke regarding Bungie, the parent company, as they LOVE the number 7; it\'s one of their leitmotif, you could say. So I wanted to post this review when I hit the 7777h mark.\r\n\r\nThe latest edit just made the joke null. Oh well...\r\n\r\nTHE REVIEW:\r\n\r\nOk, now to the review. So I played this game even before it was brought to Steam, back in the days it was on Blizzard\'s Battle Launcher. I like to think that I\'m a veteran in terms of the information I have on the game, both lore-wise and mechanics-wise. (Even if I\'m still sh*t at PvP, but that\'s between us...). So I will pass onto you some of the main things to know about the game before starting it. And I hope you will enjoy it!', 3),
