(35, 17, 'This game gave me crippling depression', 5),
(35, 23, 'Buggy mess that is 85% chores 15% fun, 50% loading 50% gameplay if you\'re lucky.', 1),
(35, 33, NULL, NULL),
(36, 2, 'Came back after I stopped playing somewhere around Season of Arrivals. So about 1.5 years ago. I played a good bit of D1 and a lot of D2 and this Expansion is at least on par with TTK and Forsaken, which are considered among the best updates. I myself had fun playing the campaign and learning about the lore for the first time in Destiny. The game still has some issues but compared to when I left it, feels like a 180 in the right direction.\r\n\r\nUnfortunately, the experience for new players still isn\'t well structured and fails to offer a clear and all around cohesive way into the mid/endgame for most people. The community has got your back tho and provides great tools to help players along the way (these are more or less required, if you want to enjoy your experience in the long run, easy to find via google).\r\nPlaying with randos is a bit hit and miss, which is not unusual but soloing is definitely a viable and fun option. Nevertheless having a premade group or at least some reliable steam buddies, certainly improves almost every aspect of the game.\r\n\r\nThe game still looks great but for a lot of people the performance seems to have worsened over the last few months or years. Not the case for me, 5700XT, 5800X, 32 GB RAM, SSD - 1440p @ ~120fps. I cannot play at maxed out settings but high to highest + some increased Render Resolution depending on the content.', 4),
(37, 2, 'First Impressions\r\nChicken Invaders 2 (CI2) is apparently part of a series of games that I had no prior experience with, but is one that\'s well-liked by many. I don\'t know where the idea of an invading force of chickens came from, but many games have drawn from strange sources when creating enemies and objectives. It hasn\'t seemed to put people off, and may have been the sort of oddity that lured people in long enough to try it and find enjoyable.\r\n\r\n\r\nGameplay\r\nWith the title drawing from Space Invaders, the gameplay is similar in that CI2 is a SHMUP, and the enemy force loads in at the start of each wave. However, there\'s no bases to hunker behind for protection. Your defense is best exhibited with a strong offense, which is granted through various projectile styles and upgrades you can pick up. There are 3 different weapon types: red bullets that spread out across the screen, a tighter cluster of green waves, and a thinner laser beam. Personally, I preferred anything other than the spread-out bullets, because the attacks were so weak. You also have a limited amount of rockets, which are best reserved for later in the game, as the difficulty increases.', 4),
(37, 7, 'Chicken Invaders 2 is a shoot ‘em up game developed by InterAction studios. This is the 2nd game in the series. The first Chicken Invaders was release well over 15 years ago so a lot of people, like me, who play this game will have nostalgia if they played the first one back in the day. The game has Alien invaders type gameplay where you’re on a ship defending earth against these evil space chickens.', 5),
(37, 18, ' just had to re-buy this title, i remember playing on my fat hp computer back in 2003. Its just so much damn fun I had to revisit its nostalgia again! Ah the memories of booting this game up on my PC when i got home from school!', 5),
(37, 22, 'Locked to 30FPS, chicken movement is random and can cause unavoidable death in many circumstances.\r\nHas no Borderless or even windowed mode and the mouse cursor can go off screen causing you too accidentally minimize the game, other games in the series also have this problem but they aren\'t locked to 30FPS and have much more fair gameplay.\r\nFor this reason I cannot recommend Chicken Invaders 2, grab the other ones instead.', 2),
(37, 23, 'Classic Game i loved this game as a kid and i still enjoy it now as an adult :D', 5),
(38, 1, 'Chicken Invaders 2 is a shoot ‘em up game developed by InterAction studios. This is the 2nd game in the series. The first Chicken Invaders was release well over 15 years ago so a lot of people, like me, who play this game will have nostalgia if they played the first one back in the day. The game has Alien invaders type gameplay where you’re on a ship defending earth against these evil space chickens.\r\n\r\nGraphics:\r\n\r\nThe game features regular run of the mill graphics which are okay for this arcade type gameplay. They’re not that pleasing to the eyes. The FPS is also locked at 30 which is always a bad thing.\r\n\r\nSound:\r\n\r\nWhile the music is very nice there’s not much variety of it. The sound effects like chicken dying can be hilarious but hearing them again and again can be pretty annoying.\r\n\r\nGameplay:\r\n\r\nThe gameplay of this game is very simple. It’s very simple to Alien invaders game where you get a bunch of enemies trying to kill you. You’re on the ship and you get 5 lives. The enemy chickens come in a few different varieties like parachuting chickens, regular chickens. Other than chickens you will frequently get asteroid waves. The chickens lay eggs which can kill you, so you must avoid these. You cannot shoot them you must avoid them. Since you can move anywhere on the screen with your mouse, dodging these slow moving eggs is not that difficult. The asteroid waves will throw a whole bunch of asteroids at you and you must avoid these.', 4),
(38, 2, 'GUYS\r\n\r\nwe picked this one up in the summer sale. all 3 of us decided to jump on and we had so much fun. not that its just fun the game is funny in itself with its jokes and gameplay. it sort of brought back our memorys of our old school gaming days :)\r\n\r\ncheck out some of our game play :)\r\n\r\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=z0qgO5vp2nA', 5),
(38, 5, 'SPOILERS AHEAD!!! IF YOU WANT TO GO BLIND INTO THE GAME YOURSELF THEN READ THIS REVIEW AFTERWARDS! ! !\r\n\r\nHave you ever wanted to shoot chicken in space while also eating drumsticks and burgers while doing so? Then this game is for you, this and every other chicken invaders games are easily one of the best space invaders clones/parodies you can find, this one is also seemingly the hardest of the 5 (if you don\'t count universe since that game is more of a spinoff), the food isn\'t the only collectible in this game though, you can also collect coins (small (bronze), medium (silver) and large (golden), the smaller ones give you 100 points, medium ones give you 1,000 and the large ones give you 10,000, but that\'s not all, you can also collect various power ups in this game (they are basically presented into these differently colored present boxes)', 4),
(38, 7, 'Its been 10 years since i have played this game for the first time, and is still awesome after those many years.\r\nIs still a fun game regardless its age.\r\nDid you ever wanted to shoot chickens in the space? Now you can.\r\nThis game brings up good memories\r\n5/5.', 5),
(38, 8, 'Childhood in a nutshell.', 4),
(38, 28, 'Brilliant fun, if you ever wanted to shoot chickens in space while collecting drumsticks and battling random aliens.\r\nFunny cutscenes, fun gameplay well worth the buy', 5),
