(40, 2, 'This game is awesome. 1-4 player co-op chaos. Personally, a minimum of 2 people to play the game because in single player you control 2 chefs which can be difficult to manage. The game features 7 chapters to cook through with a 4th star unlocked after beating the game. I aim for at least 3 stars on every level otherwise the game will be done in about 6 hours. I have bought the DLCs for the game which add a lot of content to the game. If you are just getting into overcooked now, I would recommend buying \"Overcooked: all you can eat\" which includes Overcooked 1 and 2.\r\nCan\'t wait for Overcooked 3', 5),
(40, 5, '200 character summary\r\nOvercooked 2 is an amazingly chaotic management game for up to 4 players, chop the ingredients and cook them as fast as possible for a nice tip, There are a ton of recipes and surprising kitchens.\r\n\r\nStory & Characters 8/10\r\nThe story is set in The Onion Kingdom, The Onion King read from an old book and he summoned these undead loafs of bread called the Unbread, They are hungry and will consume the entire Kingdom if they are not fed in time. You play as one of the many available chefs and it is your job to feed the Unbread to save the world. The story plays out trough some dialogue from the king after certain stages, The story is nothing special, but it is a funny universe and it should give you a laugh or 2.\r\n\r\nThe Onion king his dog and all playable characters are extremely likable, They don\'t say much but they all look very funny, If you are a shark a mouse or something way crazier, It will have a friendly face. The enemies are a little disturbing but also quite funny, Undead loafs of Bread, It probably won\'t give you or your children nightmares.', 4),
(40, 19, 'WHERE IS THE LAMB SAUCE!?!?\r\n ', 4),
(40, 20, 'I am a 45 yo father, probably one of the oldest people playing this game. I am a single father to my daughter, who is 14 now. My daughter got this game for Christmas from her uncle, so we installed it on her computer and she started playing. By the end of the week she had 24 hours on this game. This was horrible for me, as it was already hard for me to find ways to spend time with my daughter, as she is always out with her friends or just, watching YouTube. So i decided to make a Steam account and get this game to see if I could maybe play alongside her. loaded into the game, made my character and world and started playing but I was stuck on what you where supposed to do. I asked my daughter for help and she hosted a game for me to join. loved it as it was the best time had spent with my daughter since my wife had died. This game has ever since brought me and my daughter closer again and now we actually spend time together outside the house together as well. This game reminded me that there\'s fun to be had in everything, and it has brought both me and my daughter many happy memories.', 5),
