(42, 36, 'really fun game, would recommend if you are new to pegging and want to improve', 5),
(43, 4, 'This is NOT the Zuma you remember. There used to be special levels unlocked after you finished the normal levels. Challenge levels of a particular high quality that were oftentimes far better than the normal levels and worthy of repeated plays. Those levels have been removed and instead they give you \"Zen-Zuma\" --- just keep playing the same level over and over from the normal levels. It sucks. The challenge levels were precisely why I bought the game years and years ago on CD-Rom.... remember those?\r\n\r\nEA has ruined a perfectly good game by nerfing exactly what made it worthwhile. I honestly wish they had never purchased the original company that created Zuma.', 2),
(43, 6, 'This game saved my life.\r\n\r\nI am 38.\r\n\r\nMy ex-wife left me for my other ex-wife.\r\n\r\nWhen we were going through our separation, I found myself lost and miserable. I was self destructive. I got so mad one day from everything spiraling out of my control that I punched some concrete in a moment of overwhelming emotion. That caused me to break my 5th metacarpal in my right hand... my working hand... my games hand.. the hand that I held and carried my children to bed with.. The hand I desperately needed to make sure I could continue to provide.\r\n\r\nAfter learning of the severity of my self-inflicted damage, I was borderline suicidal. Keep in mind that just a few months before this, I was the happiest man with no history of depression or anxiety. I have never had fits of rage, or been one to break down and cry, but I was in a low spot that just really buried me from being able to see the light on the other side.\r\n\r\nHaving nothing better to do, I searched for a game I could play, ONE HANDED while I recovered. I somehow stumbled upon this game and read some of the reviews. I decided that it had to be worth a shot... I must admit, I didn\'t beat the game, or play nearly as long as some of you. In fact, I may have only played this game a day or two.. With that being said, after doing so, I had a new found joy and hope for life. I was able to put behind me the pain and suffering that had been cast over me.', 5),
(43, 7, 'POV: Es 2004 y tienes 8 años, vienes llegando de la escuela y después de tomar una once de cereal con leche, te sientas frente a tu PC con Windows XP a hacer tu tarea utilizando el Encarta, al terminar, te pones a jugar Zuma Deluxe.\r\nEras feliz y no lo sabias.', 4),
(43, 8, 'Without any doubt, this is my number #1 childhood game! If I\'m not wrong, it\'s even the first game I\'ve ever played on my first computer. Buying it on Steam, it brought me so much nostalgia and many funny memories. I used to play this game among with my whole family 13 years ago. I was the youngest member of the family, but one of the best at this game. This game used to be very hard for us, but now it was easy as a pie. I finished it in 2 hours with not many fails and I managed to complete the last level with 16 lives left. When I was a child, I could barely complete the last level after a lot of tries with only one life left and with a lot of frustration. I definitely recommend this awesome game to everyone!', 4),
