(48, 6, 'As much as I enjoy playing as Gaige, the Mechromancer, I\'m in between of recommending and not recommending the DLC.\r\n\r\nDeathtrap is what makes up my mind to not recommend it, he\'s too buggy that he\'s barely being useful (at least that is what I feel).\r\n\r\n1. Deathtrap uses Buck Up when you are in Fight For Your Life (FFYL), which purposes to be useless as he won\'t be regenerating your shield.\r\n2. If you are shooting an enemy at a long distance, Deathtrap won\'t even bother helping you out, instead he would just stand still doing nothing while waiting for his time to burn out.\r\n3. Sometimes when you summon Deathtrap, he tends to chase other enemy that is within his sights that you don\'t intend to pick a fight with. I find this very frustrating.\r\n4. Deathtrap dies very quick in higher level of difficulty. Few shots and he\'s dead.\r\n5. Deathtrap sometimes cast Robot Rampage at rather bad time which sometimes won\'t even hit the enemy he\'s targeting.\r\n6. Upon casting One Two Boom, Deathtrap sometimes forget what he\'s summoned for. Doings exactly nothing after unleashing the orb when the enemy is right near him.\r\n7. I always find Deathtrap using The Stare at the wrong enemy (with fire resistance) or Crystallisk (which is immune to damage dealth other than its critical spots).\r\n8. Deathtrap initiates and/or enters a fight badly timed. It sucks to have him blocking my view when I\'m shooting an enemy and the case is even worse when I\'m nearly having my FFYL gauge depleted and he blocks, ', 2),
(48, 13, 'Great DLC Highly\r\nrecommended.', 5),
(49, 6, 'I wouldn\'t describe Hammerlock\'s Big Game Hunt as a \"must have DLC\" for Borderlands 2, but it\'s not quite as horrible as a lot of the reviews make it out to be. If you\'re buying it as part of the Game of the Year edition (and you should be), then this DLC adds quite a bit of content and a unique area with a cool look to it. Even if you already have Borderlands 2, the content is worth a few bucks so pick it up when it goes on one of its frequent sales.\r\n\r\nThe enemies are a lot harder to fight, but they\'re manageable — especially if you\'re playing co-op or if you have leveled up your character pretty high and have a lot of good gear and skills in your arsenal. I won\'t say the witch doctors and Jackenstein aren\'t total pains-in-the-ass though, and I can definitely see where this would frustrate players out of continuing and finishing the DLC.\r\n\r\nThe swamp boats are completely useless in my opinion, it\'s easier just to slog around on foot — where at least you are well-armed. Unfortunately, a lot of the rare loot drops in this DLC are skins for the boats you really don\'t need to use.\r\n', 3),
(49, 13, 'Shortest DLC (around 2-3 hours), but with the hardest raid boss. The enemy in this Dlc is funny,too. Nothing more to say.', 4);
